=======================================================================
  20. FULL END-TO-END FLOW
=======================================================================

  --- STEP 1: LOGIN ---

  Browser
       | POST /api/auth/login  { username: "alice", password: "secret" }
       v
  [API Gateway]
       |   Route to auth-service
       |   No token validation (this IS the login endpoint)
       v
  [Auth Service — SecurityFilterChain]
       |   /api/auth/login is in permitAll() list
       |   Request passes through filter chain without auth check
       v
  [AuthController.login()]
       |   authManager.authenticate(
       |       new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken("alice","secret"))
       v
  [ProviderManager]
       |   Tries each provider
       |   DaoAuthenticationProvider.supports(UPAT.class) = true
       v
  [DaoAuthenticationProvider]
       |   userDetailsService.loadUserByUsername("alice")
       |       --> DB query --> returns UserDetails
       |   passwordEncoder.matches("secret", "$2a$12$...")
       |       --> BCrypt verify --> true
       v
  [Authentication object created]
       |   principal   = UserDetails (alice)
       |   credentials = [cleared]
       |   authorities = [ROLE_USER]
       |   authenticated = true
       v
  [JwtTokenService.generateToken(auth)]
       |   Build claims: sub=alice, iss=auth.myapp.com, exp=+60min
       |                 roles=[ROLE_USER], jti=uuid
       |   Sign with RSA private key from server keystore
       |   Return: "eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6Im..."
       v
  Response: HTTP 200
  Body: { "access_token": "eyJ...", "refresh_token": "...", "expires_in": 3600 }


  --- STEP 2: AUTHENTICATED REQUEST ---

  Browser
       | GET /api/orders/42
       | Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIs...
       v
  [API Gateway]
       |   BearerTokenAuthenticationFilter extracts token
       |   JwtDecoder validates: signature OK, not expired, issuer OK
       |   TokenRelay filter: copies Authorization header to downstream
       |   Adds X-User-Id: alice (optional, if pattern A)
       v
  [Order Service — filter chain starts]
       |
       | [SecurityContextHolderFilter]
       |     No existing context (stateless)
       |
       | [BearerTokenAuthenticationFilter]
       |     Extracts "eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIs..." from header
       |     Creates BearerTokenAuthenticationToken (unauthenticated)
       |     Calls authenticationManager.authenticate(token)
       |
       | [JwtAuthenticationProvider]
       |     JwtDecoder.decode(tokenValue)
       |         checks signature against public key / JWKS
       |         checks exp (not expired)
       |         checks iss (matches configured issuer)
       |         checks aud (matches this service)
       |     On success: returns Jwt object
       |     JwtAuthenticationConverter maps roles claim -> authorities
       |     Returns JwtAuthenticationToken (authenticated=true)
       |
       | [SecurityContextHolder.setAuthentication(token)]
       |     Thread now knows who the caller is
       |
       | [ExceptionTranslationFilter]
       |     No exception so far, passes through
       |
       | [AuthorizationFilter]
       |     URL rule: /api/orders/** requires authenticated()
       |     Authentication.isAuthenticated() = true  -->  PASS
       |     @PreAuthorize("#id == authentication.name") evaluated
       |         #id = 42, authentication.name = "alice"
       |         42 != "alice"  -->  PASS (different check)
       |
  [DispatcherServlet -> OrderController]
       |
       | @GetMapping("/api/orders/{id}")
       | public Order getOrder(
       |         @PathVariable Long id,
       |         @AuthenticationPrincipal Jwt jwt) {
       |     String caller = jwt.getSubject();  // "alice"
       |     return orderService.findById(id);
       | }
       v
  [Service -> Repository -> Database]
       v
  Response: HTTP 200  { "id": 42, "items": [...] }


  --- STEP 3: EXPIRED TOKEN ---

  Browser
       | GET /api/orders/42
       | Authorization: Bearer eyJ... (expired)
       v
  [API Gateway]
       |   JwtDecoder validates token
       |   exp claim is in the past
       |   Throws JwtValidationException
       v
  [ExceptionTranslationFilter]
       |   Calls AuthenticationEntryPoint
       v
  Response: HTTP 401  { "error": "Unauthorized", "message": "JWT expired" }

  (Request never reaches microservice)


  --- STEP 4: INSUFFICIENT PERMISSIONS ---

  Browser
       | DELETE /api/admin/users/5
       | Authorization: Bearer eyJ...  (valid, ROLE_USER only)
       v
  [Order Service filter chain]
       |   JWT valid, Authentication created, ROLE_USER set
       |
       | [AuthorizationFilter]
       |     URL rule: /api/admin/** requires hasRole("ADMIN")
       |     User has ROLE_USER only  -->  FAIL
       |     Throws AccessDeniedException
       |
       | [ExceptionTranslationFilter]
       |     User IS authenticated  -->  calls AccessDeniedHandler
       v
  Response: HTTP 403  { "error": "Forbidden", "message": "Access Denied" }


